## Brand Voice Development Workflow

- [ ] 1. Brand personality: Define the human personality traits of the brand
- [ ] 2. Voice attributes: Define 3-5 core voice dimensions (e.g., bold vs. subtle, formal vs. casual)
- [ ] 3. Tone by context: Define how voice shifts by situation (professional, playful, urgent, etc.)
- [ ] 4. Vocabulary: Define approved words, phrases, and terminology — and what to avoid
- [ ] 5. Writing rules: Punctuation, capitalization, emoji usage, formatting conventions
- [ ] 6. Examples: Write before/after examples showing voice in action
- [ ] 7. Audit existing content: Assess current copy against the voice guide

## Key Inputs
- Brand: {{brand_name}}
- Target audience: {{target_audience}}
- Competitor voices: {{competitor_voices}}
- Existing copy samples: {{existing_copy_samples}}
